      <div class="panel" id="sites"> <h3>What Is Microfinance</h3>

                      <a> Microfinance program</a>
			                    <p>Since its inception period (July, 2002) WSC has been implementing Micro-finance program
			                        as its major component. WSC has followed the Grameen Bank Model to operate the Micro-finance
			                        program.The aim of the program is to uplift the socio-economic conditions of the poor mainly
			                        the women. By August, 2011 over 8,000 poor women of Katmandu district have been benefited
			                        from this program. The number of women involve in the program is increasing gradually both
			                         at rural and urban areas. In total 371 Women Support Microfinance Centers (WSMFC) have been
			                         established in 29 VDCs and two Metropolitan Cities.
			                        Due to low income level and poor lifestyle of women , the have faced different types of
			                        social discrimination not only in Nepal but also in the world. because of parental property
			                       right to daughters, they do not possess land and house due to which they cannot borrow loan
			                       from bank or financial institution because such financial institution needs collateral in
			                        term of assets like land and house to borrow loan. So WSC is providing Microfinance services
			                       in door steps of poor women to uplift their socio economic status with group collateral.
			                   </p>

